================================================================================
Third-party open-source components
================================================================================

This product depends on, and (for some) redistributes in binary form,
third-party open-source software. Each such component remains under its own
license. The authoritative, version-pinned list is produced by the build
manifests:

  - Rust:    Cargo.toml / Cargo.lock
  - Android: apps/android/gradle/libs.versions.toml and the Gradle build

A curated overview of the principal components and the rationale for their
selection is maintained in docs/technical/architecture.md (§2).

Principal components and their commonly published licenses (verify against
the manifests, which are the source of truth):

  - RustCrypto crates (argon2, chacha20poly1305, hkdf, hmac, sha1, sha2,
    zeroize, subtle, getrandom) ............ MIT OR Apache-2.0
  - ciborium, serde, serde_bytes, anyhow ... MIT OR Apache-2.0
  - Mozilla UniFFI ......................... MPL-2.0
  - Java Native Access (JNA) ............... Apache-2.0 OR LGPL-2.1+
  - AndroidX / Jetpack (Compose, lifecycle,
    biometric, fragment, activity) ......... Apache-2.0
  - Kotlin stdlib & coroutines ............. Apache-2.0
  - ZXing core / zxing-android-embedded .... Apache-2.0

If you redistribute this product, you must comply with the attribution and
